'''康科德'''（{{lang-en|Concord}}）是[[美國|美國]][[麻薩諸塞州|麻薩諸塞州]][[米德爾塞克斯縣_(麻薩諸塞州)|米德爾塞克斯縣]]的一個鎮。根據[[2010年美國人口普查|2010年美國人口普查]]，該鎮人口為17,668人。<ref name="Census 2010">{{Cite web| url=http://factfinder2.census.gov| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (DP-1): Concord town, Middlesex County, Massachusetts| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=2012-04-06| archive-date=2013-09-11| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130911234518/http://factfinder2.census.gov/| dead-url=no}}</ref>[[美國人口普查局|美國人口普查局]]將康科德歸為[[大波士頓|大波士頓]]的一部份。康科德在[[美國歷史|美國歷史]]與[[美國文學|文學]]上扮演著重要的角色。

==歷史==
===史前與創立===
[[File:Egg_Rock_Inscription.jpg|left]]
這塊位於{{le|薩德伯里河|Sudbury River|薩德伯里}}和{{le|阿薩伯特河|Assabet River}}交匯處的區域，最初被稱為馬斯克特奎德（Musketaquid）。<ref name="Musketaquid">{{cite web | last =  | first =  | url = http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9025094/Concord#195620.hook | title = Concord | work =  | publisher = Encyclopædia Britannica | accessdate = 2007-04-09 | archive-date = 2007-10-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20071016154159/http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9025094/Concord#195620.hook | dead-url = no }}</ref>馬斯克特奎德是[[阿爾岡昆語族|阿爾岡昆語族]]中「草地」之意，正與該地的低窪[[河流濕地|河流濕地]]和[[鍋穴|鍋穴]]相符。<ref>{{cite web|title=Native Americans, Colonial Settlement, and the Concord River|url=http://lowelllandtrust.org/greenwayclassroom/history/nativeamer.htm|work=Lowell Land Trust|accessdate=2013-07-28|archive-date=2020-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919205356/https://lowelllandtrust.org/greenwayclassroom/history/nativeamer.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>美國原住民曾在當地種植玉米；河流魚產豐富，土地草木茂盛且適於耕種。<ref name="Bulkeley">{{cite web
 |last= 
 |first= 
 |url=http://www.newenglandancestors.org/education/articles/research/special_guests/member_staff/peter_bulkeley_deacon_and_co_founder_of_concord_m_659_517.asp 
 |title=Peter Bulkeley: Settlement in Concord 
 |work= 
 |publisher=New England Historic Genealogical Society 
 |accessdate=2007-04-09 
 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927032104/http://www.newenglandancestors.org/education/articles/research/special_guests/member_staff/peter_bulkeley_deacon_and_co_founder_of_concord_m_659_517.asp 
 |archivedate=2007-09-27 
 |deadurl=yes 
}}</ref>然而，歐洲人將[[天花|天花]][[鼠疫|鼠疫]]帶往了美洲，使得該地人口有著很大程度的減少。<ref name="Shattuck">{{cite web|last=Shattuck |first=Lemuel |url=http://ftp.rootsweb.com/pub/usgenweb/ma/middlesex/towns/concord/histch01.txt |title=History of the Town of Concord, Mass |publisher=RootsWeb |work= |year=1835 |accessdate=2007-04-09 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071120161419/http://ftp.rootsweb.com/pub/usgenweb/ma/middlesex/towns/concord/histch01.txt |archivedate=2007-11-20 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

1635年，一群來自英國的移民在牧師{{le|彼得·巴爾克利|Peter Bulkley}}和少校{{le|西蒙·威拉德 (第一代)|Simon Willard (first generation)|西蒙·威拉德}}的帶領之下，與當地部落的殘存者洽談收購土地。巴爾克利是一位有影響力的宗教領袖，他曾帶著多位種植園主進入森林；<ref>{{Citation| author =Moses Coit Tyler| year =1883 | title =A History of American Literature | publisher =G. P. Putnam's Sons |accessdate=2013-07-28}}</ref>威拉德是一位精明的商人，他會講阿爾岡昆語，且獲得了美國原住民的信任。<ref>{{Citation|title=Simon Willard's Life In Concord|author= Marian H. Wheeler|publisher= Willard Family Association|accessdate=2013-07-28}}</ref>他們買下6平方英里的土地，形成了這座全新城鎮的基礎，並為了答謝這筆交易和平落幕，因而將此地命名為「康科德」。<ref name="Musketaquid"/>

===列星頓和康科特戰役===
{{main|列星頓和康科特戰役}}
[[列星頓和康科特戰役|列星頓和康科特戰役]]是[[美國獨立戰爭|美國獨立戰爭]]的第一場戰役。1775年4月19日，一支[[英國陸軍|英國陸軍]][[正規軍|正規軍]]從[[波士頓|波士頓]]行軍至康科德，搜索傳聞貯藏鎮上的武器。來自[[保羅·列維爾|保羅·列維爾]]和其他信使的事先警告，讓殖民地居民集結準備反抗。在一場清晨於列星頓開出戰役第一槍的小衝突後，英國遠征隊在{{le|法蘭西斯·史密斯 (英國陸軍軍官)|Francis Smith (British Army officer)|法蘭西斯·史密斯陸軍中校}}的帶領下抵達了康科德。康科德與周圍城鎮的居民（特別是一間來自{{le|阿克頓 (麻薩諸塞州)|Acton, Massachusetts|阿克頓}}由{{le|艾薩克·戴維斯 (士兵)|Isaac Davis (soldier)|艾薩克·戴維斯}}帶領的高級鑽頭公司）在{{le|老北橋|Old North Bridge}}[[列克星敦和康科德战役#康科德的徵收行動與北橋戰事|擊退了一支英國分遣隊]]，迫使英軍撤退。<ref name="LOC">{{cite web | last =  | first =  | url = http://memory.loc.gov/ammem/today/apr19.html | title = Today In History: April 19th | work =  | publisher = The Library of Congress | accessdate = 2007-04-03 | archive-date = 2007-03-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070302164826/http://memory.loc.gov/ammem/today/apr19.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>隨後，來自各地的民兵在英軍返回波士頓的途中[[列克星敦和康科德战役#英軍撤退與民兵追擊|襲擊了他們]]，最終展開[[波士頓之圍|波士頓之圍]]，並引發了這場戰役。

殖民地居民最初將這場戰役描繪成是英國人殘暴及侵略的一個例子：一份殖民地的報導抨擊這是「英國軍隊的血腥屠殺」。<ref name="Randolph">{{cite book | last = Randolph | first = Ryan | url = http://books.google.com/books?id=DItAX0GNQpwC&pg=PT85&lpg=PT85&dq=%22coffin+broadside%22+-jackson#PPT86,M1 | title = Paul Revere and the Minutemen of the American Revolution | work = | publisher = The Rosen Publishing Group via Google Books | accessdate = 2007-04-09}}</ref>然而經過了一個世紀後，美國人仍對這場戰役記憶猶新，將愛國的、幾近虛構的（將老北橋發出的槍聲形容是「震撼世界」）情懷訴諸文學作品，像是《{{le|康科特頌|Concord Hymn}}》和《{{le|列維爾之夜行|Paul Revere's Ride (poem)}}》。<ref name="Revere">{{cite web|last=Gioia |first=Dana |url=http://www.danagioia.net/essays/elongfellow.htm |title="On "Paul Revere's Ride" by Henry Wadsworth Longfellow" |work= |publisher= |accessdate=2007-04-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070203195658/http://www.danagioia.net/essays/elongfellow.htm |archivedate=2007-02-03 }}</ref>該鎮在1975年4月舉辦了這場戰役的兩百周年紀念慶典，總統[[傑拉爾德·福特|傑拉爾德·福特]]巡遊至老北橋並發表了演說。<ref name="Ford">{{cite web | last =  | first =  | url = http://www.mass.gov/lib/ | title = Featured Resource: Photograph Collection 374 | work =  | publisher = The State Library of Massachusetts | accessdate = 2007-04-09 | archive-date = 2007-02-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070221042633/http://www.mass.gov/lib/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

